HEADWORD: Prolicide
<hw>Prol"i*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proles</ets> offspring + <ets>caedere</ets> to kill.]</ety>
<def>The crime of destroying one's offspring, either in the womb or
after birth.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

